1
00:00:08,513 --> 00:00:11,382
<i>My life has always been ordinary.</i>

2
00:00:12,383 --> 00:00:13,952
<i>Something not even worth mentioning.</i>

3
00:00:16,187 --> 00:00:18,056
<i>Whether I remember it or not,</i>

4
00:00:20,291 --> 00:00:21,626
<i>it was never anything special.</i>

5
00:00:23,962 --> 00:00:25,096
<i>No,</i>

6
00:00:25,163 --> 00:00:27,298
<i>if anything,</i>

7
00:00:27,365 --> 00:00:29,200
<i>it's full of memories I'd rather forget.</i>

8
00:00:33,738 --> 00:00:35,573
<i>As a kid,</i>

9
00:00:35,640 --> 00:00:38,276
<i>I never had the courage</i>
<i>to stand up to the bullies.</i>

10
00:00:38,843 --> 00:00:42,213
<i>A girl with a strong sense of justice</i>
<i>just happened to pass by and save me.</i>

11
00:00:46,317 --> 00:00:47,952
<i>And I fell in love for the first time.</i>

12
00:00:50,989 --> 00:00:54,425
<i>But I couldn't even thank her.</i>

13
00:00:58,429 --> 00:01:00,999
<i>In the end, I never worked up</i>
<i>the courage to speak to her.</i>

14
00:01:03,468 --> 00:01:04,369
<i>No matter how long</i>

15
00:01:05,203 --> 00:01:08,907
<i>I waited, the love of my life never came.</i>

16
00:01:11,342 --> 00:01:12,777
<i>I was always just an observer.</i>

17
00:01:15,413 --> 00:01:16,548
<i>That was my life.</i>

18
00:01:19,017 --> 00:01:20,618
<i>And I thought I was okay with it.</i>

19
00:01:23,955 --> 00:01:24,923
<i>But…</i>

20
00:01:27,458 --> 00:01:28,826
<i>the day I met you…</i>

21
00:01:44,943 --> 00:01:46,311
<i>my life…</i>

22
00:01:47,979 --> 00:01:49,180
<i>had changed.</i>

23
00:02:00,124 --> 00:02:05,129
We opened our directly operated
Meguro store on the first of last month,

24
00:02:05,196 --> 00:02:09,767
and we've added 13 new retailers.

25
00:02:09,834 --> 00:02:11,236
We now have 62 locations--

26
00:02:11,302 --> 00:02:14,072
We still don't have enough locations
in central Tokyo.

27
00:02:14,706 --> 00:02:17,342
What about a major shopping complex
attached to a terminal station?

28
00:02:17,408 --> 00:02:19,077
Is there any chance of getting
into NEWoMan Takanawa?

29
00:02:20,278 --> 00:02:22,180
We've approached them several times.

30
00:02:22,247 --> 00:02:24,816
-It isn't so easy--
-Whether Velel gets into that location

31
00:02:24,882 --> 00:02:27,118
could change the company's
overall sales by two or 3%.

32
00:02:27,685 --> 00:02:30,121
IZUMI TAKEDA - MARIKO'S SECRETARY

33
00:02:32,824 --> 00:02:35,159
-Are you saying you can't do it?
-Oh, no,

34
00:02:35,760 --> 00:02:36,594
I'll do my best.

35
00:02:37,228 --> 00:02:38,596
-Please do.
-Yes.

36
00:02:39,464 --> 00:02:41,532
-She's scary…
-Continuing…

37
00:02:41,599 --> 00:02:43,101
TAKUMI SANO, SECOND BRAND DIVISION
RYOKO HASHIMOTO, SECOND BRAND DIVISION

38
00:02:43,868 --> 00:02:45,703
Please schedule a meeting
with Ms. Hara from NEWoMan.

39
00:02:45,770 --> 00:02:46,904
I'll speak with her personally.

40
00:02:46,971 --> 00:02:48,306
Understood.

41
00:02:48,373 --> 00:02:52,010
I'd like to discuss this
with the branch's president.

42
00:02:52,076 --> 00:02:53,311
Make sure you tell them that.

43
00:02:53,378 --> 00:02:55,113
-I will let them know.
-Did you hear?

44
00:02:55,179 --> 00:02:57,215
Apparently, Mariko has seriously started

45
00:02:57,282 --> 00:02:59,984
-looking for a husband.
-What? Really?

46
00:03:01,953 --> 00:03:02,787
-Excuse me.
-I hear

47
00:03:02,854 --> 00:03:05,323
-she's been on some dates already.
-What? Seriously?

48
00:03:37,755 --> 00:03:40,591
Another date that didn't go well?

49
00:03:42,427 --> 00:03:44,462
Don't say "another".

50
00:03:44,529 --> 00:03:45,697
So I was right.

51
00:03:47,899 --> 00:03:51,469
I mean, we just had nothing in common.

52
00:03:52,270 --> 00:03:55,139
He asked me what I do on my days off,

53
00:03:55,206 --> 00:03:56,674
so I said I watch movies,

54
00:03:56,741 --> 00:03:59,377
and from there, he spent the rest
of the conversation talking about <i>Top Gun.</i>

55
00:03:59,444 --> 00:04:01,879
He was trying to connect with you.

56
00:04:01,946 --> 00:04:03,748
I've never even seen <i>Top Gun.</i>

57
00:04:03,815 --> 00:04:06,351
When I told him that, he said, "Seriously?

58
00:04:06,417 --> 00:04:08,186
You're missing out on life!"

59
00:04:08,252 --> 00:04:11,389
Yes, I know that type of person.

60
00:04:11,456 --> 00:04:14,325
-They're annoying, aren't they?
-Yes, I know.

61
00:04:14,392 --> 00:04:17,195
But this time, it's your fault.

62
00:04:18,096 --> 00:04:19,263
What? Why?

63
00:04:19,330 --> 00:04:22,166
Because you only watch
Marvel superhero movies.

64
00:04:23,735 --> 00:04:27,438
You don't watch movies on your day off.

65
00:04:27,505 --> 00:04:30,007
You have to say Marvel movies.

66
00:04:30,074 --> 00:04:31,743
That's why he brought up <i>Top Gun.</i>

67
00:04:35,380 --> 00:04:39,150
Still, that's what dating for marriage is.

68
00:04:40,284 --> 00:04:43,888
It's about figuring out each other's
boring parts and weird quirks,

69
00:04:43,955 --> 00:04:46,257
then finding someone
you can compromise with.

70
00:04:47,692 --> 00:04:49,394
That's marriage hunting.

71
00:04:51,362 --> 00:04:55,166
Though I guess it's funny hearing that
from someone who's divorced.

72
00:04:57,368 --> 00:04:59,270
But it's okay.

73
00:05:01,272 --> 00:05:03,908
My marriage gave me
the greatest treasure of my life.

74
00:05:09,514 --> 00:05:10,648
You don't seriously

75
00:05:11,249 --> 00:05:16,554
expect to meet someone
where you instantly click, do you?

76
00:05:17,855 --> 00:05:23,494
You don't actually believe in destiny,
do you?

77
00:05:24,896 --> 00:05:27,698
Of course not. I don't believe in that.

78
00:05:27,765 --> 00:05:29,233
Let me assure you.

79
00:05:29,934 --> 00:05:31,602
There's no such thing.

80
00:05:39,977 --> 00:05:40,978
Thank you for waiting.

81
00:05:41,045 --> 00:05:42,980
Here's the daily lunch special.

82
00:05:43,047 --> 00:05:44,348
Thank you very much.

83
00:05:48,252 --> 00:05:49,620
-Thank you.
-Sure.

84
00:05:50,721 --> 00:05:54,659
VELEL BEGINS ITS SKINCARE DEPARTMENT

85
00:05:54,725 --> 00:05:57,261
DAD: CAN WE TALK ABOUT
THAT PROPOSAL FROM THE OTHER DAY?

86
00:06:01,699 --> 00:06:03,367
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

87
00:06:03,434 --> 00:06:04,569
-Credit card, please.
-Okay.

88
00:06:05,336 --> 00:06:08,339
That'll be 2,000 yen.

89
00:06:08,406 --> 00:06:09,240
-Okay.
-Thank you.

90
00:06:10,208 --> 00:06:12,176
-Okay.
-Just touch here, please.

91
00:06:16,214 --> 00:06:17,615
-Ah, one more time, please.
-Okay.

92
00:06:20,451 --> 00:06:23,554
Sorry. I think the machine just broke.

93
00:06:24,355 --> 00:06:26,224
Sorry, do you have cash?

94
00:06:27,458 --> 00:06:29,527
I didn't bring any cash.

95
00:06:31,062 --> 00:06:32,830
-I'm sorry.
-Well then…

96
00:06:32,897 --> 00:06:34,131
You can put hers together with mine.

97
00:06:34,699 --> 00:06:35,867
No, you don't have to.

98
00:06:37,401 --> 00:06:38,236
Together.

99
00:06:39,203 --> 00:06:40,037
Thank you.

100
00:06:41,472 --> 00:06:42,373
Okay then…

101
00:06:42,440 --> 00:06:44,509
-All right, thank you.
-Sure.

102
00:06:49,180 --> 00:06:50,581
-Excuse me!
-Yes?

103
00:06:51,616 --> 00:06:53,150
-Thank you very much.
-No, not at all.

104
00:06:54,252 --> 00:06:56,454
I can send it back to you
with a payment app.

105
00:06:56,521 --> 00:06:57,488
That's okay.

106
00:06:57,555 --> 00:07:01,292
I can't let a complete stranger
pay for my lunch.

107
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:05,196
Would you rather have cash?

108
00:07:05,263 --> 00:07:07,431
If so, I can send it to you later.

109
00:07:07,498 --> 00:07:09,267
Just give me your contact information

110
00:07:14,772 --> 00:07:16,040
Um…

111
00:07:16,741 --> 00:07:18,109
I'm not trying to do anything.

112
00:07:19,410 --> 00:07:21,646
-I'm sorry.
-I know.

113
00:07:24,815 --> 00:07:26,083
You know?

114
00:07:37,662 --> 00:07:40,798
GINJIRO NOSE
MARIKO'S FATHER AND PRESIDENT

115
00:07:40,865 --> 00:07:43,301
VELEL BEGINS ITS SKINCARE DEPARTMENT

116
00:07:47,371 --> 00:07:48,839
Your cost estimates are too optimistic.

117
00:07:50,241 --> 00:07:52,777
You should be able to lower
the production cost further.

118
00:07:52,843 --> 00:07:53,678
Understood.

119
00:07:54,679 --> 00:07:56,147
The ingredients aren't that great either.

120
00:07:56,714 --> 00:07:58,215
GOTA ASAI, GINJIRO'S SECRETARY

121
00:07:58,282 --> 00:08:01,752
As it stands, I don't see how launching
a skincare line under Velel

122
00:08:01,819 --> 00:08:04,055
has much chance of succeeding.

123
00:08:06,090 --> 00:08:06,958
I understand.

124
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:11,195
Revise it before the executive meeting.

125
00:08:14,665 --> 00:08:15,733
Thank you very much.

126
00:08:20,404 --> 00:08:21,405
It's been decided?

127
00:08:21,472 --> 00:08:22,640
Pretty much.

128
00:08:22,707 --> 00:08:24,575
-You did it!
-You really did.

129
00:08:24,642 --> 00:08:27,011
If we add skincare alongside makeup,

130
00:08:27,078 --> 00:08:29,380
Velel could become
the company's top brand.

131
00:08:29,447 --> 00:08:30,948
I hope it sells!

132
00:08:31,015 --> 00:08:32,083
It definitely will!

133
00:08:32,149 --> 00:08:33,851
Stem cells are really popular right now.

134
00:08:33,918 --> 00:08:35,853
Nothing has been decided yet.

135
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,221
We still have a lot of issues to solve.

136
00:08:42,126 --> 00:08:43,694
I see.

137
00:08:43,761 --> 00:08:46,163
So the ingredients need
to be rethought as well.

138
00:08:48,232 --> 00:08:51,769
Using PDRN as-is doesn't make us unique.

139
00:08:53,137 --> 00:08:54,438
We need something original…

140
00:09:00,611 --> 00:09:02,780
I heard.

141
00:09:02,847 --> 00:09:06,384
Velel's starting a skincare division, huh?

142
00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:07,284
Congratulations.

143
00:09:08,619 --> 00:09:11,822
-Nothing has been decided yet.
-It practically has.

144
00:09:12,757 --> 00:09:14,625
People say you and the president
don't get along,

145
00:09:15,126 --> 00:09:19,296
but I guess he still
has a soft spot for his daughter.

146
00:09:38,082 --> 00:09:40,051
<i>‎Doors are closing.</i>

147
00:09:40,985 --> 00:09:42,620
-I'm sorry.
-Excuse me.

148
00:09:42,687 --> 00:09:43,521
Sorry.

149
00:09:49,493 --> 00:09:50,895
Sorry about that.

150
00:09:55,299 --> 00:09:57,501
So you said "I know"
because you're our employee?

151
00:10:00,171 --> 00:10:01,005
Excuse me.

152
00:10:01,072 --> 00:10:03,441
Oh, wait.

153
00:10:03,507 --> 00:10:04,341
For lunch…

154
00:10:04,408 --> 00:10:07,178
-Really, don't worry about it.
-No.

155
00:10:07,244 --> 00:10:09,246
There's no reason for you to buy me lunch.

156
00:10:10,548 --> 00:10:12,717
-Thanks for helping me.
-Okay then…

157
00:10:15,086 --> 00:10:18,122
Oh, uh, this isn't mine.

158
00:10:18,789 --> 00:10:19,490
‎SKINCARE MARKET RESEARCH

159
00:10:19,557 --> 00:10:21,959
That's mine.

160
00:10:23,661 --> 00:10:25,162
You did this?

161
00:10:26,997 --> 00:10:30,434
There have been a lot of Korean products

162
00:10:30,501 --> 00:10:33,270
using stem cell culture
supernatant lately,

163
00:10:33,337 --> 00:10:36,874
so I thought I'd learn more about it.

164
00:10:43,280 --> 00:10:45,549
If we combine it
with plant-derived stem cells,

165
00:10:45,616 --> 00:10:48,185
I think we could develop
something ourselves.

166
00:10:48,252 --> 00:10:50,254
We could get ahead of the competition.

167
00:10:53,324 --> 00:10:56,494
Ah, sorry, I shouldn't act like
I know what I'm talking about.

168
00:10:58,429 --> 00:11:00,030
Which department do you work in?

169
00:11:01,766 --> 00:11:03,467
<i>Going up.</i>

170
00:11:04,135 --> 00:11:05,469
These are the approval documents

171
00:11:05,536 --> 00:11:07,838
for our current product
development projects.

172
00:11:07,905 --> 00:11:09,340
Who's that?

173
00:11:09,406 --> 00:11:12,309
I think he's Yukimura
from General Affairs.

174
00:11:12,376 --> 00:11:13,177
‎SOTA YUKIMURA, GENERAL AFFAIRS

175
00:11:13,244 --> 00:11:16,480
People in General Affairs
say he's completely harmless.

176
00:11:16,547 --> 00:11:17,948
The invisible type.

177
00:11:18,015 --> 00:11:22,686
So why is this invisible guy
joining our department?

178
00:11:23,621 --> 00:11:25,956
If you have any questions, just ask.

179
00:11:26,023 --> 00:11:26,857
Um…

180
00:11:28,058 --> 00:11:30,127
Why was I transferred here?

181
00:11:30,795 --> 00:11:34,565
Because Mariko believes
you're someone who could come in handy.

182
00:11:44,942 --> 00:11:46,310
Look, look. Mariko's here.

183
00:11:47,378 --> 00:11:49,380
-Hey.
-Yes?

184
00:11:51,282 --> 00:11:54,151
Could you write a proposal after looking
into whether we could use those

185
00:11:54,218 --> 00:11:56,687
plant-derived stem cell ingredients
you mentioned the other day?

186
00:11:56,754 --> 00:12:01,625
Oh, uh, well, the papers
I read didn't include

187
00:12:01,692 --> 00:12:03,427
-any in vivo test results.
-So you can't do it?

188
00:12:03,494 --> 00:12:04,528
No, no.

189
00:12:05,262 --> 00:12:06,263
I can if I have the data.

190
00:12:06,831 --> 00:12:09,733
I ordered some. I'll send it to you later.

191
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:11,068
Thank you.

192
00:12:25,850 --> 00:12:26,917
I understand.

193
00:12:27,751 --> 00:12:30,287
Mariko is a bit scary, isn't she?

194
00:12:30,354 --> 00:12:33,290
I couldn't even tell
why she was angry just now.

195
00:12:33,357 --> 00:12:36,794
Was she angry? I thought
she was just giving me instructions.

196
00:12:38,262 --> 00:12:41,832
Yukimura, are you one of those people
who's weirdly immune to pressure?

197
00:12:43,601 --> 00:12:44,435
I'm not sure.

198
00:12:51,342 --> 00:12:52,877
I'm surprised.

199
00:12:52,943 --> 00:12:55,179
So that's your type, huh?

200
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,082
-What are you talking about?
-Yukimura.

201
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:00,618
What?

202
00:13:00,684 --> 00:13:04,121
It's the first time I've ever seen you
take an interest in someone.

203
00:13:04,188 --> 00:13:05,623
Only professionally.

204
00:13:05,689 --> 00:13:07,758
-Oh, look, look.
-Stop that.

205
00:13:07,825 --> 00:13:10,761
-You're blushing.
-Honestly…

206
00:13:11,328 --> 00:13:14,398
Wow, a guy like him, huh…

207
00:13:14,465 --> 00:13:15,799
GRANDMA: COME SEE ME AFTER WORK,
I HAVE SOMETHING IMPORTANT TO TALK ABOUT

208
00:13:30,614 --> 00:13:33,050
AKIKO NOSE, MARIKO'S GRANDMOTHER

209
00:13:34,251 --> 00:13:36,420
So, what's the important thing?

210
00:13:37,054 --> 00:13:40,257
Your grandma has finally met
her person of destiny.

211
00:13:41,058 --> 00:13:42,026
What?

212
00:13:42,092 --> 00:13:44,795
I stopped by one of our clients today,

213
00:13:44,862 --> 00:13:48,532
and on the way home, I found a man
at a vegetable stand selling potatoes,

214
00:13:48,599 --> 00:13:51,135
and he said, "They're only 500 yen."

215
00:13:51,201 --> 00:13:52,136
I see…

216
00:13:52,202 --> 00:13:55,673
But they got so heavy,
I couldn't continue walking.

217
00:13:55,739 --> 00:13:57,341
Really? Are you okay?

218
00:13:57,408 --> 00:14:01,445
A wonderful young man
happened to come by and help me.

219
00:14:03,747 --> 00:14:05,649
Your person of destiny is a young man?

220
00:14:06,717 --> 00:14:09,553
Older than you, I'd say.

221
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:14,158
He's a good person.

222
00:14:14,224 --> 00:14:17,328
Perfect husband material for you.

223
00:14:17,394 --> 00:14:20,397
Is that what this was about?

224
00:14:20,464 --> 00:14:22,166
You're looking for someone
to marry, aren't you?

225
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:24,101
Or have you found someone already?

226
00:14:25,002 --> 00:14:26,103
No, but…

227
00:14:26,170 --> 00:14:29,406
I arranged for the three of us
to meet tomorrow.

228
00:14:30,641 --> 00:14:31,709
What?!

229
00:14:32,276 --> 00:14:34,611
Why would you do that without asking me?

230
00:14:34,678 --> 00:14:35,913
-Like I said, it's for your…
-What?

231
00:14:36,513 --> 00:14:37,915
Mariko's proposal?

232
00:14:39,616 --> 00:14:42,052
I think the president
intends to approve it.

233
00:14:42,119 --> 00:14:43,887
If that happens,

234
00:14:43,954 --> 00:14:46,924
her position inside the company
will only get stronger!

235
00:14:46,991 --> 00:14:48,258
What have you been doing?

236
00:14:48,993 --> 00:14:50,361
I'm sorry.

237
00:14:50,427 --> 00:14:51,628
<i>Keito won't be joining the company</i>

238
00:14:51,695 --> 00:14:54,965
and becoming an executive
for another five years.

239
00:14:55,833 --> 00:14:57,668
Stop this, no matter what it takes.

240
00:14:57,735 --> 00:14:58,902
I know.

241
00:14:59,636 --> 00:15:01,105
I've already set things in motion.

242
00:15:02,239 --> 00:15:03,340
Are you sure about this?

243
00:15:03,407 --> 00:15:06,610
You don't even know who the man is.

244
00:15:07,177 --> 00:15:09,446
-Oh, sis! You're here.
-Yes.

245
00:15:09,513 --> 00:15:12,549
That serum sample you gave me
the other day was great.

246
00:15:12,616 --> 00:15:14,051
Can I have another one?

247
00:15:14,118 --> 00:15:16,086
-Another one?
-Please. One more. Please.

248
00:15:17,087 --> 00:15:19,189
-Hello.
-Sure, fine…

249
00:15:19,256 --> 00:15:21,291
Oh, Mariko, you're here.

250
00:15:21,358 --> 00:15:22,192
Yes.

251
00:15:22,259 --> 00:15:23,627
Have you eaten yet?

252
00:15:23,694 --> 00:15:26,530
-Why don't we have something together?
-That's right. We should.

253
00:15:26,597 --> 00:15:28,132
It's been a while
since we've all eaten together.

254
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:32,836
I'll pass. I've got plans with friends.

255
00:15:32,903 --> 00:15:35,339
Hey, Keito, you little…

256
00:15:35,406 --> 00:15:38,742
I still have work to do,
so I'd better get going.

257
00:15:38,809 --> 00:15:41,045
-I see…
-Oh, that's too bad.

258
00:15:41,111 --> 00:15:42,479
Come by again anytime.

259
00:15:54,191 --> 00:15:58,429
MARIKO

260
00:16:14,778 --> 00:16:15,779
Hey…

261
00:16:16,847 --> 00:16:18,082
I think I'm just going to leave.

262
00:16:18,148 --> 00:16:19,683
Don't worry.

263
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:20,918
He's a good man.

264
00:16:22,853 --> 00:16:24,721
Oh, over here!

265
00:16:29,393 --> 00:16:31,261
Sorry to keep you waiting.

266
00:16:39,636 --> 00:16:40,737
I'm sorry.

267
00:16:41,905 --> 00:16:44,341
I was just surprised
by how beautiful you are.

268
00:16:45,409 --> 00:16:47,578
Ah, what am I saying?

269
00:16:48,912 --> 00:16:52,116
This is my granddaughter, Mariko.

270
00:16:53,117 --> 00:16:55,285
This is Taisuke Sakura.

271
00:16:56,186 --> 00:16:59,590
-It's nice to meet you. My name is Sakura.
-Nice to meet you.

272
00:17:01,358 --> 00:17:03,861
Thank you for helping my grandmother

273
00:17:03,927 --> 00:17:05,229
-the other day.
-No, not at all.

274
00:17:07,998 --> 00:17:11,702
-Well, first, let's sit down.
-Of course.

275
00:17:14,338 --> 00:17:17,040
I forgot to ask before.

276
00:17:17,107 --> 00:17:19,843
What do you do for a living, Mr. Sakura?

277
00:17:21,445 --> 00:17:22,513
I'm a civil servant.

278
00:17:22,579 --> 00:17:24,748
Oh, that's wonderful.

279
00:17:24,815 --> 00:17:26,717
Perfect husband material.

280
00:17:26,783 --> 00:17:28,752
Grandma, don't be so pushy.

281
00:17:28,819 --> 00:17:30,220
You're making him uncomfortable.

282
00:17:31,955 --> 00:17:35,259
To be honest, I almost didn't come.

283
00:17:36,093 --> 00:17:38,762
You just suddenly wanted me
to meet your granddaughter.

284
00:17:40,063 --> 00:17:41,231
I'm very sorry.

285
00:17:42,232 --> 00:17:45,669
But I'm glad I came.

286
00:18:00,951 --> 00:18:02,052
Hello?

287
00:18:02,586 --> 00:18:04,821
I need you to do something for me.

288
00:18:15,732 --> 00:18:16,934
Good work today, everyone.

289
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,035
I'm heading out.

290
00:18:18,101 --> 00:18:19,736
-You as well.
-Have a good day.

291
00:18:20,871 --> 00:18:24,641
As always, she leaves right on time.

292
00:18:24,708 --> 00:18:27,511
That's fine. It makes it easier
for us to leave too.

293
00:18:27,578 --> 00:18:28,478
That's true.

294
00:18:30,414 --> 00:18:31,248
All right then…

295
00:18:35,219 --> 00:18:37,554
VELVEL SKINCARE PROGRESS REPORT

296
00:18:39,056 --> 00:18:40,090
Pardon me.

297
00:18:42,259 --> 00:18:43,327
Thank you.

298
00:18:44,261 --> 00:18:45,963
You've been coming here a lot lately.

299
00:18:47,531 --> 00:18:48,665
Sorry for staying so long.

300
00:18:48,732 --> 00:18:51,134
Not at all. You're always welcome.

301
00:18:53,337 --> 00:18:54,771
Take your time.

302
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,140
Good luck.

303
00:19:15,225 --> 00:19:16,126
Hello.

304
00:19:18,929 --> 00:19:20,530
I thought you'd already gone home.

305
00:19:20,597 --> 00:19:24,468
You come back to work
at night a lot, don't you?

306
00:19:25,836 --> 00:19:26,937
I was wondering.

307
00:19:27,004 --> 00:19:28,572
Do you pretend to leave on time

308
00:19:28,639 --> 00:19:32,342
so your staff will feel comfortable
going home?

309
00:19:34,611 --> 00:19:35,612
Um,

310
00:19:36,313 --> 00:19:38,315
I don't know if you'll like it, but…

311
00:19:39,383 --> 00:19:41,551
-No, isn't that for you?
-No, no,

312
00:19:41,618 --> 00:19:43,587
I bought one for myself too.

313
00:19:49,860 --> 00:19:53,030
Is this from that old
traditional-style cafe behind the office?

314
00:19:53,096 --> 00:19:56,199
Visiting cafes is one of my hobbies.

315
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:59,269
I've been there too.

316
00:20:00,837 --> 00:20:03,507
I wanted to keep it as my secret hideaway.

317
00:20:04,875 --> 00:20:07,377
Then I won't go anymore.

318
00:20:08,712 --> 00:20:13,216
What? Oh, no, that's not what I meant.

319
00:20:13,283 --> 00:20:15,752
Cafes belong to everyone.

320
00:20:24,728 --> 00:20:25,629
Your phone…

321
00:20:28,665 --> 00:20:30,901
Iguazu Falls, in Argentina.

322
00:20:31,768 --> 00:20:32,803
You've been there?

323
00:20:34,104 --> 00:20:35,005
Yes.

324
00:20:36,173 --> 00:20:40,944
Actually, it was used
as a filming location in a Marvel movie.

325
00:20:41,011 --> 00:20:42,979
I'm a huge Marvel fan.

326
00:20:44,214 --> 00:20:47,217
People think Marvel movies
are just superhero films,

327
00:20:47,951 --> 00:20:50,787
but they're actually
full of deep human drama.

328
00:20:50,854 --> 00:20:54,758
Each hero has their own
standalone story, but then they all

329
00:20:54,825 --> 00:20:59,062
come together in the Avengers movies,
like a giant puzzle.

330
00:20:59,129 --> 00:21:00,464
It's so exciting.

331
00:21:07,904 --> 00:21:09,773
Why am I getting so carried away?

332
00:21:09,840 --> 00:21:10,841
Oops.

333
00:21:14,044 --> 00:21:16,213
The Warrior Falls, from <i>Black Panther.</i>

334
00:21:21,318 --> 00:21:24,254
I've been there too.

335
00:21:28,091 --> 00:21:30,660
You're the first person I've ever
been able to have this conversation with.

336
00:21:32,863 --> 00:21:35,198
I've actually visited a lot
of other Marvel locations too.

337
00:21:35,265 --> 00:21:39,536
The first one I went to
was Grand Central Terminal in New York.

338
00:21:39,603 --> 00:21:40,871
Look, look.

339
00:21:42,773 --> 00:21:45,742
Standing there thinking,
"This is where the Avengers fought."

340
00:21:48,278 --> 00:21:49,179
Oh, sorry.

341
00:21:50,747 --> 00:21:52,349
I must seem creepy,
talking your ear off like this.

342
00:21:54,851 --> 00:21:55,719
I'm really sorry.

343
00:22:14,871 --> 00:22:16,072
What?

344
00:22:16,139 --> 00:22:18,575
What? What?

345
00:22:18,642 --> 00:22:19,676
What is this?

346
00:22:19,743 --> 00:22:22,179
It's practically identical to ours.

347
00:22:22,245 --> 00:22:24,114
Mr. Tateiwa's team

348
00:22:24,181 --> 00:22:26,650
already submitted this proposal
to the company.

349
00:22:26,716 --> 00:22:28,652
No way. They totally stole it.

350
00:22:28,718 --> 00:22:32,923
Apparently, they've already secured
a major partnership too.

351
00:22:33,890 --> 00:22:35,759
I don't think we have any chance now.

352
00:22:39,362 --> 00:22:41,498
Aren't you ashamed using
such underhanded tactics?

353
00:22:41,565 --> 00:22:42,866
Underhanded?

354
00:22:42,933 --> 00:22:44,267
What are you talking about?

355
00:22:44,901 --> 00:22:48,238
You're the ones who came up
with a similar proposal afterward

356
00:22:50,006 --> 00:22:55,812
and tried to use your influence
as the president's daughter to steal ours.

357
00:22:55,879 --> 00:22:57,948
-What are you talking about?
-You…

358
00:22:59,182 --> 00:23:02,452
…really believe you're here
because of your own ability, don't you?

359
00:23:04,888 --> 00:23:07,757
A spoiled little rich girl like you
should know her place.

360
00:23:47,964 --> 00:23:49,933
You can stop.

361
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,468
There's no point anymore.

362
00:23:54,838 --> 00:23:56,006
I know.

363
00:23:56,940 --> 00:23:58,074
But I still want to see it through.

364
00:24:03,280 --> 00:24:04,414
I'VE ATTACHED SUPPORTING MATERIALS

365
00:24:04,481 --> 00:24:05,615
PLEASE CHECK
THE SEPARATE DOCUMENT. YUKIMURA

366
00:24:09,753 --> 00:24:12,956
It's useless! None of this matters!

367
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:18,395
I know.

368
00:24:20,730 --> 00:24:22,799
I know how serious…

369
00:24:24,167 --> 00:24:25,969
and how much time you've devoted…

370
00:24:29,673 --> 00:24:30,574
to this project.

371
00:24:41,718 --> 00:24:42,752
What?

372
00:25:25,362 --> 00:25:26,262
Excuse me.

373
00:25:33,603 --> 00:25:34,437
What?

374
00:25:34,504 --> 00:25:37,340
I was planning to approve
Tateiwa's project,

375
00:25:38,775 --> 00:25:39,909
but we're going with yours.

376
00:25:41,144 --> 00:25:43,546
-Why all of a sudden?
-Where are the documents?

377
00:25:45,015 --> 00:25:46,683
They're all ready.

378
00:25:46,750 --> 00:25:50,754
We'll announce it officially
at the executive meeting, then.

379
00:25:54,124 --> 00:25:55,258
Thank you.

380
00:25:58,695 --> 00:25:59,996
<i>Congratulations!</i>

381
00:26:00,063 --> 00:26:01,798
It got approved.

382
00:26:01,865 --> 00:26:02,699
Yes.

383
00:26:03,199 --> 00:26:05,035
How did that happen?

384
00:26:05,101 --> 00:26:06,503
Seriously. What changed all of a sudden?

385
00:26:06,569 --> 00:26:08,538
-Right?
-But…

386
00:26:09,239 --> 00:26:10,640
-Yay!
-Yay!

387
00:26:10,707 --> 00:26:11,841
-Yay!
-That's great!

388
00:26:11,908 --> 00:26:13,576
-All right! That's great!
-That's great, that's great!

389
00:26:13,643 --> 00:26:14,778
-Yes!
-Yes.

390
00:26:14,844 --> 00:26:16,579
It's still too early to celebrate.

391
00:26:17,247 --> 00:26:20,316
Contact the research lab immediately
and begin developing the formulation.

392
00:26:20,383 --> 00:26:21,384
-Okay.
-Okay.

393
00:26:21,451 --> 00:26:23,953
Once they have the formulation down,

394
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:27,657
being strategizing on PR
to get the biggest pull of consumers.

395
00:26:28,391 --> 00:26:31,761
<i>There's no one at our company</i>
<i>who doesn't know Mariko.</i>

396
00:26:35,065 --> 00:26:36,433
Please get me an appointment

397
00:26:36,499 --> 00:26:38,201
with the supervisor of that.
I'll speak with them.

398
00:26:38,268 --> 00:26:40,036
Understood.

399
00:26:40,103 --> 00:26:43,640
<i>She's always the center of attention,</i>
<i>someone who lives in the spotlight.</i>

400
00:26:46,176 --> 00:26:48,645
<i>I was always content…</i>

401
00:26:51,715 --> 00:26:53,917
<i>just watching her from afar.</i>

402
00:26:54,751 --> 00:26:56,553
-I will let them know.
-Did you hear?

403
00:26:56,619 --> 00:26:58,221
Apparently, Mariko has seriously started

404
00:26:58,288 --> 00:27:00,657
-looking for a husband.
-What? Really?

405
00:27:02,625 --> 00:27:04,227
<i>A day like this would of course come.</i>

406
00:27:05,361 --> 00:27:06,496
Welcome in.

407
00:27:06,563 --> 00:27:07,664
Take your time.

408
00:27:08,898 --> 00:27:10,033
<i>I knew someone other than me</i>

409
00:27:11,601 --> 00:27:13,169
<i>would one day be sitting beside her.</i>

410
00:27:15,071 --> 00:27:18,475
<i>I thought I was prepared, but it hurt…</i>

411
00:27:21,377 --> 00:27:22,645
<i>more than I expected.</i>

412
00:27:24,647 --> 00:27:26,516
<i>Watching Mariko from afar…</i>

413
00:27:27,784 --> 00:27:29,185
<i>That was enough.</i>

414
00:27:29,753 --> 00:27:31,087
Sorry.

415
00:27:31,154 --> 00:27:33,957
-I think the machine just broke.
-<i>It should have…</i>

416
00:27:35,024 --> 00:27:36,826
Do you have cash?

417
00:27:36,893 --> 00:27:38,928
I didn't bring any cash.

418
00:27:41,064 --> 00:27:42,732
<i>I thought it would be enough.</i>

419
00:27:46,603 --> 00:27:47,971
You can put hers together with mine.

420
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,975
No, you don't have to.

421
00:27:53,109 --> 00:27:54,244
<i>Life…</i>

422
00:27:54,310 --> 00:27:56,112
It definitely will! Stem cells

423
00:27:56,179 --> 00:27:58,948
-are really popular right now.
-<i>…sometimes changes unexpectedly.</i>

424
00:27:59,449 --> 00:28:00,884
We still have a lot of issues to solve.

425
00:28:02,619 --> 00:28:04,821
<i>I want to help Mariko.</i>

426
00:28:05,321 --> 00:28:07,857
‎GENERAL AFFAIRS DEPARTMENT

427
00:28:09,826 --> 00:28:11,461
TRENDING INGREDIENTS IN KOREA 2026

428
00:28:11,528 --> 00:28:12,862
<i>I just want to help her.</i>

429
00:28:13,930 --> 00:28:15,498
SKINCARE MARKET RESEARCH

430
00:28:30,914 --> 00:28:33,883
<i>-Really, that's all.</i>
-I'm sorry.

431
00:28:34,584 --> 00:28:35,485
What?

432
00:28:36,586 --> 00:28:38,755
TRANSFER TO THE BRAND DIVISION

433
00:28:43,359 --> 00:28:45,361
<i>I want Mariko to be happy.</i>

434
00:28:45,428 --> 00:28:47,797
PHOTOOS

435
00:28:47,864 --> 00:28:49,532
MARIKO

436
00:28:49,599 --> 00:28:50,867
A NEW FAV SPOT I FOUND

437
00:28:50,934 --> 00:28:52,268
THE ATMOSPHERE IS SO GREAT
YOU FORGET ABOUT TIME

438
00:28:52,836 --> 00:28:54,370
<i>That's all.</i>

439
00:28:54,437 --> 00:28:55,839
ANCIENT FOLK HOUSE
WOOD HEARTH

440
00:28:55,905 --> 00:28:58,041
Is this from that old
traditional-style cafe behind the office?

441
00:28:58,107 --> 00:29:00,009
Visiting cafes is one of my hobbies.

442
00:29:01,211 --> 00:29:06,049
You really believe you're here
because of your own ability, don't you?

443
00:29:07,016 --> 00:29:10,220
A spoiled little rich girl
like you should know her place.

444
00:29:18,728 --> 00:29:19,829
<i>Mariko…</i>

445
00:29:24,434 --> 00:29:26,269
<i>Mariko is hurt,</i>

446
00:29:28,071 --> 00:29:30,206
<i>and I'm just watching.</i>

447
00:29:33,610 --> 00:29:34,978
APPLICANT: TSUYOSHI TATEIWA

448
00:29:36,813 --> 00:29:37,814
<i>No.</i>

449
00:29:37,881 --> 00:29:38,948
TSUYOSHI TATIEWA'S PROPOSAL
TO NOSE COSMETICS

450
00:29:39,015 --> 00:29:40,617
<i>I have to protect Mariko.</i>

451
00:29:44,621 --> 00:29:45,989
<i>I will make sure.</i>

452
00:29:47,223 --> 00:29:48,157
<i>I will.</i>

453
00:29:53,363 --> 00:29:54,197
Excuse me.

454
00:30:02,338 --> 00:30:06,843
I have evidence that you
obtained that partnership through fraud.

455
00:30:07,510 --> 00:30:08,411
Who the hell are you?

456
00:30:08,478 --> 00:30:09,846
PLEASE WALK YOUR BICYCLE

457
00:30:09,913 --> 00:30:14,350
If you don't want this exposed,
withdraw from the new project.

458
00:30:15,018 --> 00:30:16,219
What?

459
00:30:16,286 --> 00:30:18,288
You claimed you landed
the partnership legitimately,

460
00:30:19,188 --> 00:30:22,125
but you paid money to the agency
with company funds, didn't you?

461
00:30:22,191 --> 00:30:27,096
This transfer labeled "preliminary market
research expenses" is suspicious.

462
00:30:27,664 --> 00:30:29,432
-Also…
-You…

463
00:30:30,533 --> 00:30:31,901
work in the brand division, don't you?

464
00:30:33,469 --> 00:30:35,104
Did that spoiled princess
put you up to this?

465
00:30:36,172 --> 00:30:38,841
If this comes to light,
you won't just lose your job.

466
00:30:38,908 --> 00:30:40,376
You'll be facing criminal charges.

467
00:30:41,844 --> 00:30:42,845
Hey!

468
00:30:47,250 --> 00:30:49,352
How did you even get those documents?

469
00:30:51,020 --> 00:30:55,158
You're the one who illegally
accessed company data.

470
00:31:00,430 --> 00:31:01,497
Mariko

471
00:31:02,932 --> 00:31:06,102
isn't treated specially just because she's
the president's daughter. She works hard.

472
00:31:08,071 --> 00:31:09,472
Harder than anyone else.

473
00:31:11,941 --> 00:31:15,578
Every single day, she works
with everything she's got.

474
00:31:18,081 --> 00:31:19,082
I don't get what you mean.

475
00:31:24,020 --> 00:31:26,923
-Hey.
-Please, withdraw.

476
00:31:28,157 --> 00:31:31,561
If you withdraw, I won't tell anyone.
Please, withdraw.

477
00:31:31,627 --> 00:31:32,595
Get out of my way.

478
00:31:33,863 --> 00:31:37,433
-Hey! Let go. Let go!
-Please, withdraw. Please!

479
00:31:39,135 --> 00:31:40,570
What is wrong with you?

480
00:31:41,504 --> 00:31:43,172
Are you crazy or something?

481
00:31:44,841 --> 00:31:46,609
-Hey.
-Please withdraw.

482
00:31:47,377 --> 00:31:48,478
Please withdraw!

483
00:31:48,544 --> 00:31:50,413
Please! Please!

484
00:31:51,214 --> 00:31:52,048
Please withdraw!

485
00:31:57,220 --> 00:31:58,287
I won't tell anyone.

486
00:32:07,363 --> 00:32:11,868
Please continue with the strategy
for PR that we have.

487
00:32:11,934 --> 00:32:16,439
Please decide the release date
by next Friday with Izumi.

488
00:32:16,506 --> 00:32:17,840
-Okay.
-Understood.

489
00:32:20,877 --> 00:32:22,478
Huh? What happened to your mouth?

490
00:32:24,013 --> 00:32:25,548
I just fell a little.

491
00:32:26,949 --> 00:32:28,584
How do you fall hard enough
to cut yourself like that?

492
00:32:29,719 --> 00:32:30,620
I know, right?

493
00:32:46,335 --> 00:32:47,336
Hey, wait!

494
00:32:49,672 --> 00:32:50,506
Uh, yes?

495
00:32:51,007 --> 00:32:53,509
I only called your name.

496
00:32:53,576 --> 00:32:54,677
Don't be so nervous.

497
00:32:56,212 --> 00:32:57,046
Sorry.

498
00:33:01,150 --> 00:33:02,185
You're the reason.

499
00:33:05,988 --> 00:33:07,056
I mean,

500
00:33:08,991 --> 00:33:13,029
things worked out
because you insisted on finishing

501
00:33:13,096 --> 00:33:14,330
those presentation materials.

502
00:33:20,169 --> 00:33:21,270
Thank you.

503
00:33:51,400 --> 00:33:52,635
Come inside.

504
00:33:53,402 --> 00:33:55,238
Excuse me.

505
00:33:56,839 --> 00:33:58,141
I'm starving.

506
00:33:58,207 --> 00:34:00,409
I picked up a few things. Want to eat?

507
00:34:00,476 --> 00:34:02,378
Yes, thanks.

508
00:34:02,879 --> 00:34:04,714
-So?
-Hm?

509
00:34:04,780 --> 00:34:06,282
What's it like

510
00:34:06,349 --> 00:34:09,085
finally getting noticed by the girl
you've been in love with?

511
00:34:12,522 --> 00:34:18,094
My heart's filled with equal parts
happiness and guilt.

512
00:34:18,761 --> 00:34:19,629
What does that mean?

513
00:34:20,530 --> 00:34:22,331
You haven't done
something crazy, have you?

514
00:34:24,934 --> 00:34:26,302
What? That's scary, you know.

515
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:28,671
Oh, thank you.

516
00:34:29,906 --> 00:34:30,940
All right.

517
00:34:31,807 --> 00:34:33,976
-Let's eat!
-Let's eat.

518
00:34:34,777 --> 00:34:37,513
So, do you actually think
you've got a chance?

519
00:34:38,614 --> 00:34:40,583
Hmm…

520
00:34:42,852 --> 00:34:43,986
-Hey.
-Mm?

521
00:34:46,289 --> 00:34:49,292
Do you think anyone
is born liking cilantro?

522
00:34:49,792 --> 00:34:50,793
Huh?

523
00:34:50,860 --> 00:34:53,095
Years ago, my boss took me
to a Thai restaurant.

524
00:34:53,162 --> 00:34:55,464
It was the first time
I'd ever eaten cilantro.

525
00:34:56,365 --> 00:34:58,201
He loved it.

526
00:34:58,267 --> 00:35:04,040
But I couldn't stand the smell
or the taste.

527
00:35:05,608 --> 00:35:07,877
I think that's how most
Japanese people feel.

528
00:35:08,477 --> 00:35:11,247
You want to be the kind of foodie
who enjoys Thai food,

529
00:35:11,314 --> 00:35:12,381
but without the cilantro.

530
00:35:12,448 --> 00:35:15,551
So you remove it
from your salad before mixing it in.

531
00:35:15,618 --> 00:35:17,687
I guess if the other person likes it,
they can just take it, right?

532
00:35:19,021 --> 00:35:21,190
But there's always someone who says,

533
00:35:22,291 --> 00:35:24,227
"Come on, just try one bite."

534
00:35:25,494 --> 00:35:28,998
As you know, I'm terrible at saying no.

535
00:35:29,799 --> 00:35:33,502
So instead of refusing,
I held my breath and ate it.

536
00:35:37,540 --> 00:35:42,245
Then the next time we went out,
he said, "Oh, yes, you liked this stuff."

537
00:35:42,311 --> 00:35:45,181
So he kept putting more on my plate.

538
00:35:45,748 --> 00:35:47,016
Where is this story going?

539
00:35:47,083 --> 00:35:48,451
Keep that up, and who knows.

540
00:35:49,285 --> 00:35:50,486
Before I knew it,

541
00:35:51,254 --> 00:35:53,756
I became the kind of man
who buys cilantro salad.

542
00:35:56,425 --> 00:35:58,294
I wasn't born liking it.

543
00:35:59,095 --> 00:36:02,031
But if something
is always there, everywhere,

544
00:36:02,999 --> 00:36:04,967
you start eating it without realizing.

545
00:36:08,771 --> 00:36:10,306
Before you know it, you actually like it.

546
00:36:13,476 --> 00:36:15,444
Do you think I could become her cilantro?

547
00:36:16,779 --> 00:36:19,048
I've been told to try it
plenty of times, and I still hate it.

548
00:36:22,718 --> 00:36:26,455
I can't believe you've stayed in love
with the same girl for 25 years.

549
00:36:26,522 --> 00:36:27,690
I could never do that.

550
00:36:28,891 --> 00:36:30,826
I mean, it's scary.

551
00:36:30,893 --> 00:36:34,530
You think it'd make her happy
if she knew it'd been 25 years?

552
00:36:35,197 --> 00:36:36,699
Me? Never.

553
00:36:38,801 --> 00:36:39,869
Mariko…

554
00:36:43,339 --> 00:36:45,007
saved me.

555
00:36:49,712 --> 00:36:51,180
I'm exhausted.

556
00:37:29,919 --> 00:37:32,555
JAPONICA WORKBOOK

557
00:37:37,059 --> 00:37:38,127
<i>May 7.</i>

558
00:37:39,462 --> 00:37:41,097
<i>Something great happened today.</i>

559
00:37:47,570 --> 00:37:48,404
<i>Like always,</i>

560
00:37:49,171 --> 00:37:53,342
<i>Nakamura and the other boys</i>
<i>from Class Three were bullying me.</i>

561
00:37:53,409 --> 00:37:54,777
-Hey, you.
-What?

562
00:37:55,378 --> 00:37:57,380
<i>A girl passing by saved me.</i>

563
00:38:01,650 --> 00:38:03,119
<i>She was so strong.</i>

564
00:38:04,353 --> 00:38:06,255
<i>So cool.</i>

565
00:38:07,156 --> 00:38:09,358
MARIKO NOSE

566
00:38:24,039 --> 00:38:25,107
<i>May 10.</i>

567
00:38:25,975 --> 00:38:29,178
<i>It looks like she goes</i>
<i>to a private elementary school.</i>

568
00:38:30,646 --> 00:38:32,615
<i>I want to thank her, but…</i>

569
00:38:49,365 --> 00:38:50,900
Cute…

570
00:39:12,054 --> 00:39:13,422
<i>I can't do it.</i>

571
00:39:13,489 --> 00:39:15,825
<i>I can't talk to her.</i>

572
00:39:18,194 --> 00:39:20,095
TRAFFIC SAFETY

573
00:39:24,333 --> 00:39:27,670
Somebody! Somebody help! Let me go!

574
00:39:28,637 --> 00:39:31,407
Somebody! Somebody! Let me go!

575
00:39:31,474 --> 00:39:33,676
Help me! Let me go!

576
00:39:37,046 --> 00:39:40,082
Somebody! Somebody, please come!

577
00:39:40,649 --> 00:39:42,418
Somebody, please help!

578
00:39:42,485 --> 00:39:44,587
Please come out! Somebody!

579
00:39:44,653 --> 00:39:47,356
-Hey! What's wrong?
-Help! That girl!

580
00:39:48,157 --> 00:39:49,758
Whoa! Hey!

581
00:39:49,825 --> 00:39:51,660
What are you doing? Stop!

582
00:39:56,131 --> 00:39:58,300
<i>Even though she was so strong,</i>

583
00:39:58,367 --> 00:39:59,802
<i>the girl who saved me…</i>

584
00:40:01,136 --> 00:40:02,938
<i>almost became a victim herself.</i>

585
00:40:06,308 --> 00:40:09,211
DIARY

586
00:40:11,080 --> 00:40:12,414
<i>I've decided.</i>

587
00:40:13,516 --> 00:40:15,985
<i>I'll protect that girl, no matter what.</i>

588
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:18,954
MATH DRILLS

589
00:40:22,324 --> 00:40:23,392
<i>I'll always stay by her side.</i>

590
00:40:25,160 --> 00:40:26,262
<i>Always.</i>

591
00:40:27,429 --> 00:40:29,164
SOTA YUKIMURA

592
00:40:31,333 --> 00:40:32,167
SCHOOL ENTRANCE CEREMONY

593
00:40:32,234 --> 00:40:33,168
<i>April 6.</i>

594
00:40:33,736 --> 00:40:35,938
<i>I got into the same</i>
<i>middle school as Mariko.</i>

595
00:40:38,040 --> 00:40:39,675
<i>Our classrooms are as far apart</i>
<i>as they could be,</i>

596
00:40:41,510 --> 00:40:43,779
<i>but she's closer to me than ever before.</i>

597
00:40:49,585 --> 00:40:50,586
<i>I got into</i>

598
00:40:50,653 --> 00:40:54,189
<i>the same high school as Mariko</i>
<i>through the escalator system,</i>

599
00:40:54,256 --> 00:40:56,525
<i>but it won't be so easy going forward.</i>

600
00:40:56,592 --> 00:41:02,197
<i>Mariko has the best grades,</i>
<i>so I have to work very hard.</i>

601
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:06,001
<i>I finally got into</i>

602
00:41:06,068 --> 00:41:08,604
<i>the same university as Mariko</i>
<i>a year after she did.</i>

603
00:41:09,405 --> 00:41:12,107
<i>It's sad we're in different years,</i>

604
00:41:12,174 --> 00:41:14,877
<i>but just sharing the same campus</i>
<i>makes me happy.</i>

605
00:41:18,113 --> 00:41:19,181
<i>December 3.</i>

606
00:41:19,248 --> 00:41:19,915
CAREER COUNSELING

607
00:41:19,982 --> 00:41:22,084
<i>I want to become Mariko's junior at work.</i>

608
00:41:22,151 --> 00:41:25,120
-Which company are you applying to?
-Nose Cosmetics.

609
00:41:26,055 --> 00:41:27,590
<i>I have to get hired.</i>

610
00:41:27,656 --> 00:41:28,791
NEW-HIRE ENTRANCE CEREMONY

611
00:41:28,857 --> 00:41:30,292
<i>April 2.</i>

612
00:41:30,859 --> 00:41:32,194
<i>Today was the entrance ceremony.</i>

613
00:41:34,630 --> 00:41:37,633
<i>I managed to become Mariko's junior.</i>

614
00:41:41,070 --> 00:41:43,405
<i>Mariko's only in her second year,</i>

615
00:41:43,472 --> 00:41:46,041
<i>but she's already</i>
<i>one of the company's key employees.</i>

616
00:41:47,843 --> 00:41:50,245
<i>I have to work hard too,</i>
<i>so I can get even a little closer to her.</i>

617
00:42:01,290 --> 00:42:02,925
2026/6/19 - SOTA YUKIMURA

618
00:42:14,637 --> 00:42:16,839
<i>I've been transferred</i>
<i>into the same department as Mariko.</i>

619
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:18,807
<i>And she finally</i>

620
00:42:20,142 --> 00:42:21,810
<i>is aware of me.</i>

621
00:42:23,545 --> 00:42:25,147
<i>In these 25 years,</i>

622
00:42:25,214 --> 00:42:29,018
<i>I've never been this close to her.</i>

623
00:42:33,222 --> 00:42:34,390
<i>But this is no time to celebrate.</i>

624
00:42:34,456 --> 00:42:35,557
NO SUBJECT

625
00:42:35,624 --> 00:42:37,860
INCONSISTENCIES IN SOME EXPENSE PROCESSING
BY MR. TATEIWA

626
00:42:37,926 --> 00:42:38,894
PRELIMINARY MARKET
RESEARCH EXPENSES: 1,672,000 YEN

627
00:42:38,961 --> 00:42:42,898
<i>I must do what I need to.</i>

628
00:42:44,633 --> 00:42:46,468
President, look at this.

629
00:42:51,273 --> 00:42:53,242
SERIAL CHILD KIDNAPPER AND MURDERER
SATORU HATANO RELEASED FROM PRISON

630
00:42:57,680 --> 00:42:59,014
RELEASED AFTER 25 YEARS
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW

631
00:42:59,081 --> 00:43:00,783
"I HELD A GRUDGE AGAINST THE ENTIRE WORLD"

632
00:43:03,986 --> 00:43:05,654
RELEASED FROM PRISON

633
00:43:11,026 --> 00:43:15,164
<i>Darkness always tries to sneak</i>
<i>into things that shine light.</i>

634
00:43:21,670 --> 00:43:22,938
SATORU HATANO

635
00:43:23,005 --> 00:43:24,206
<i>But Mariko?</i>

636
00:43:25,040 --> 00:43:27,009
<i>You only deserve the light.</i>

637
00:43:28,110 --> 00:43:29,478
State of the body?

638
00:43:34,717 --> 00:43:37,886
Clear the way. Clear the way.

639
00:43:38,987 --> 00:43:40,355
-Hello.
-Hi.

640
00:43:40,422 --> 00:43:41,657
TAISUKE SAKURA

641
00:43:41,724 --> 00:43:43,692
-Murder?
-Most likely.

642
00:43:44,460 --> 00:43:47,996
Looks like a knife. The victim was stabbed
multiple times in the abdomen.

643
00:43:48,063 --> 00:43:52,067
Judging from the rigor mortis, they've
probably been dead for more than 24 hours.

644
00:43:53,969 --> 00:43:55,003
Who is the victim?

645
00:43:56,271 --> 00:43:59,441
Tsuyoshi Tateiwa.
An employee at Nose Cosmetics.

646
00:44:05,848 --> 00:44:08,083
<i>I won't forgive anyone</i>
<i>who gets in the way…</i>

647
00:44:10,219 --> 00:44:11,386
<i>of Mariko's life.</i>

648
00:44:14,523 --> 00:44:19,094
<i>For 25 years,</i>
<i>Mariko's the only one I've protected.</i>

649
00:44:19,595 --> 00:44:22,197
PLEASE CHECK THE SEPARATE DOCUMENT
YUKIMURA

650
00:44:22,998 --> 00:44:24,133
<i>But…</i>

651
00:44:25,334 --> 00:44:27,236
<i>destined love</i>

652
00:44:27,302 --> 00:44:29,304
<i>was never going to find me,</i>
<i>no matter how long I waited.</i>

653
00:44:32,040 --> 00:44:32,941
<i>So…</i>

654
00:44:35,744 --> 00:44:37,446
<i>I'll create destiny myself.</i>

655
00:44:38,046 --> 00:44:40,649
I'VE DECIDED

656
00:44:50,993 --> 00:44:54,263
I've decided that I'll become
the person you're destined to be with.

657
00:44:58,567 --> 00:44:59,635
‎NEXT TIME…

658
00:44:59,701 --> 00:45:02,704
May I speak with you for a moment?

659
00:45:08,076 --> 00:45:09,011
Subtitle translation by: Maslin Friedman

